					 <strong>Make these 3 habits and start losing weight</strong><p><span>Hi everyone, I'm 24 and I've been a chronic fat man all my life. A year ago I weighed 118 kg, today I weigh 97 kg and I'm not </span><span></span><a>going to stop </a><span>. During this time, I read a lot of literature on weight loss, </span><span><b>faced a lot </b></span><span>of problems ( </span><span><i>breakdowns, zazhora, starvation </i></span><span>), but now everything is fine, I am going to my goal of 75 kg. </span></p><p><span>On my way, I did everything, but it was these </span><span><b>three habits </b></span><span>that finally allowed me to start losing weight. </span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Useful habits for weight loss</span></figcaption></figure><h3><span>1) Go to bed on time </span></h3><p><span>Weight loss and sleep are directly related. During sleep, the body recovers strength, there is a synthesis </span><span></span><a>of sleep </a><span>hormone and growth hormone (</span><span><i>melatonin and somatropin</i></span><span>), which are responsible for </span><span><b>the utilization of adipose tissue </b></span><span>. </span></p><p><span>If you go to bed after 2 hours of the night, then the body </span><span><b>does not have time </b></span><span>to accumulate them and there are swelling, loss of strength, and the process of losing weight slows down. Therefore, try to go to bed on time. In addition, this will avoid evening runs to the refrigerator. </span></p><h3><span>2) Count every calorie</span></h3><p><span>Whatever diet you follow ( </span><span><i>low fat, protein, keto, buckwheat, and so on.</i></span><span>) if you </span><span><b>do not count calories</b></span><span>, there will be no result. You can eat extra pounds with buckwheat alone, so make a habit of keeping a food diary ( </span><span><i>at least approximately</i></span><span>). </span></p><p><span>For this purpose, mobile devices are excellent</span><span></span><a> apps </a><span>or a regular placard in Excel. Over time</span><span><b>, you will </b></span><span>learn to evaluate the caloric content of a dish by eye without using scales and apps.</span></p><h3><span>3) Learn to replace the pleasure of eating with the pleasure of living</span></h3><p><span>If you think only about the diet all the time, then you can go crazy. So here an ancient Indian principle will do just fine: </span></p><blockquote><span>What not to think of a white monkey, think of a pink elephant </span></blockquote><p><span>In my life, my only distractions have always been the computer, TV, and food. But now I </span><span><b>realized how wrong I had been. </b></span><span>Usually people eat when they are just bored. </span></p><p><span>Avoid get bored, read books, go for a walk, take up a new hobby and you will not notice how food for you will become just a tool, not an object of worship. </span></p><blockquote><span><i>Thanks for your attention.</i></span><span> </span><span></span><a><i>Subscribe to the channel </i></a><span><i>. What are your good / bad habits? Share your opinions in the comments section. More articles about health, weight loss and medicine are coming soon.</i></span><span> </span></blockquote><p><span></span></p><p><span></span></p><p><span></span></p><div></div>
					
